{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-entry-js","path":"/notes/py/data_structures/namedtuple","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Namedtuple"},"html":"<h3>Defining a NamedTuple</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>A namedtuple is an object type that is:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Easy-to-create</li>\n<li>Lightweight</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A namedtuple is a collection that has the following properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Can be <strong>ordered</strong></li>\n<li>Is <strong>indexed</strong></li>\n<li>Is <strong>immutable</strong></li>\n<li>Allows <strong>duplicates</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Named tuples can be referenced using:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Object-like variable dereferencing</li>\n<li>Standard tuple syntax</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The use-cases include the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Improve code readability by using object notation</li>\n<li>Can replace immutable classes without functions</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example of Use-Case 1</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token comment\"># Normal tuple</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> pt1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">5.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> pt2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> line <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pt1<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span>pt2<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token comment\"># Named tuple</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> collections <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> namedtuple\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> Point <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> namedtuple<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Point'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'x y'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> pt1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Point<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">5.0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> pt2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Point<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> line <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pt1<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>x<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>pt2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>x</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Example of Use-Case 2</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token comment\"># Replaceable class</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Gender</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>     <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">__init__</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> male<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> female<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>         self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>male <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> male\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>         self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>female <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> female\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> genders <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Gender<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>male<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> female<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token comment\"># Named tuple</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> collections <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> namedtuple\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> Gender <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> namedtuple<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Gender'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'male'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'female'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> genders <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Gender<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>male<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> female<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/9872434/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Benefits of Named Tuples over Dictionaries</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/collections.html#collections.Counter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">NamedTuple Documentation from the Python Standard Library</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/2970722/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">What are NamedTuples in Python?</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"py/data_structures/namedtuple","previousSlug":"py/data_structures/chainmap","nextSlug":"py/data_structures/counter","previousTitle":"ChainMap","nextTitle":"Counter"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}